        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 19 at 3:37AM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 337 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pinehill, or 12 miles southeast of Henderson, moving southwest at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Minden, Pinehill, Mount Enterprise, Laneville, Brachfield,
Glenfawn and Chapman.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
